== Fishcakes ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). When boiling add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{½}(zested and halved). Trim the @spring onions{2}(trimmed), then slice thinly. Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @hot smoked salmon{150%g} in a #bowl{}. Stir in the lemon zest, half the spring onion, half the @soured cream{150%g} and half the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g}. Season with @salt and plenty of @pepper.

Pop the remaining breadcrumbs on a #plate{}, mix with the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. When the potatoes are drained, leave them to cool for a few minutes before adding to the bowl with the salmon. Season with salt and pepper and use a #fork{} to mash everything together gently. Use your hands to start forming the mixture into two fishcakes per person. Lay the cakes in the breadcrumbs and turn to coat each side.

Line a #baking tray{} with parchment, put the fishcakes on a baking tray, drizzle with oil and bake on the top shelf of your oven till golden, ~{15-18%minutes}. Meanwhile, pop the remaining soured cream and remaining spring onion into a #small bowl{}. Add a squeeze of lemon juice, season with salt and pepper, mix together and set aside. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

About 5 mins before the fishcakes are done, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the green beans. Stir fry the beans for ~{1-2%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of water and cover with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}). Cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Once the fishcakes are cooked, divide between #plates{} and serve with the garlicky green beans, soured cream sauce and lemon wedges alongside. Enjoy!